In this speech delivered at Parris Island, SC, former First Lady Jill Biden expresses gratitude to the Marines and their families for their service and sacrifice. She shares a personal story about her father's Navy service and how it influenced her upbringing. Biden also reflects on her son Beau's decision to join the military and the impact it had on their family. She acknowledges the sacredness of choosing to serve one's country and emphasizes the importance of supporting military families. Biden mentions her initiative, Joining Forces, which aims to assist military and veteran families, caregivers, and survivors. She assures the Marines that their dedication is appreciated and that efforts are being made to ensure they never have to choose between their love of country and family. The speech concludes with gratitude for the families' support and a recognition of the significance of the Marines' choice to serve.